# {{project_name}} — Conventions

Static, project-wide conventions for every service deployed through
this harness. Values live in `config/harness.yaml`; this file explains
**why** each convention exists so contributors know when (and when
not) to depart from it.

## Source of truth

`config/harness.yaml` is the single source of truth for:

- `cluster.namespace` — k8s namespace for all deploys.
- `conventions.workspace_dir` — where service artifacts live. You
  set this via `harness init --workspace <dir>`.
- `conventions.release_name` — default `"{service}-{active_env}-v1"`.
  The `-{active_env}-` segment lets dev and prod coexist on one
  cluster without collisions.
- `conventions.label_selector` — the label every workload must carry
  (the harness uses it for `kubectl wait` / `kubectl get pods`).
- `conventions.image_tag` — the tag docker images are pushed under.
  Override per service in the chart only if that service versions
  independently.
- `environments.<env>.arch` — the target CPU arch; the harness passes
  it as `docker build --platform linux/<arch>`.

Do not duplicate these values in chart files or Dockerfiles. Read
them from YAML or rely on the harness to inject them.

## Service layout

```
{{workspace_dir}}/
├── helm/<service>/
│   ├── Chart.yaml
│   ├── values.yaml
│   ├── values-<env>.yaml
│   └── templates/
├── docker/<service>/
│   └── Dockerfile
└── tests/<phase>/
    └── smoke-test-<sub_goal>.sh
```

- A service must have at least one of `helm/` or `docker/` — both is
  fine, neither is a configuration error.
- Smoke tests are optional but recommended; they run after
  `kubectl wait` passes.

## Labels (required)

```yaml
metadata:
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: <service>      # == Chart.Name
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: <release>  # == Release.Name
    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Helm
```

The harness's `kubectl wait` and `kubectl get pods` queries use
`label_selector` to target pods — no label, no wait.

## Naming

- Service slug: `[a-z][a-z0-9-]*`, matches the folder name under
  `helm/`/`docker/` and the `**service_name**:` field in phase specs.
- Release name: computed by `conventions.release_name` — never
  hardcode.
- Image: `<registry>/<service>:<image_tag>` — assembled by the CLI.
